  "title": "LORRY DRIVER",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Driving and Vehicle Operation:</strong>Safely operate commercial vehicles for transporting goods, materials, or equipment over short or long distances.</li><li><strong>Loading and Unloading:</strong>Assist with or supervise the loading and unloading of goods, ensuring they are properly secured and protected from damage.</li><li><strong>Route and Schedule Planning:</strong>Plan efficient delivery routes and schedules in coordination with transport managers or dispatchers.</li><li><strong>Vehicle Maintenance:</strong>Conduct daily vehicle checks, including for tires, brakes, and oil, and report any issues or perform basic maintenance.</li><li><strong>Record Keeping:</strong>Maintain accurate logbooks, delivery documents, trip reports, and records of driving hours.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong>Adhere to all road haulage regulations, company policies, and traffic rules, including those for vehicle size, weight, and parking.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong>Provide reliable and courteous service to customers, representing the company professionally.</li></ul>",
